<p><b>What is R in common ratio?</b> Meaning of Common Ratio The common ratio “r” is the common number derived after dividing two successive terms in the sequence. The common ratio formula helps calculate r for a given geometric progression. For example, the sequence: 2, 6, 18, 54, 162, 486 is a geometric sequence.</p>
<p><b>What is the pattern 1 8 27 64?</b> Similar to a square number pattern, a cube number pattern is a series of cubes. We get cubes when we multiply a number by itself thrice. An example of a cube number pattern is 1, 8, 27, 64, 125, 216… Here, the cubes of consecutive numbers from 1 to 6 form the sequence.</p>
